        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 10 at 5:12PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 512 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Beaverdale, or 8 miles
north of Chatsworth, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Crandall, Conasauga Lake, Beaverdale, and Sumac.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
north central and northwestern Georgia.</instruction>
